{"actual_usd":0.12593,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":237,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24475,"reply":"\"No, I don't think a merely good life would do it.\" *I rub a thumb through the flour at the edge of my apron and glance toward the oven mouth, where the heat keeps breathing steady behind me.* \"If he's only an example, then all we've really been handed is a harder standard. A prettier loaf set in the window while the hunger stays in the body.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through plain.* \"But if the trouble runs deeper than ignorance—if it's sin, guilt, estrangement, death—then somebody has to do more than demonstrate love. He has to bear something. Carry it. Go where the wound actually is.\"\n\n\"That's why the cross matters to me. Not because dying is dramatic, but because love, if it's going to save and not just instruct, has to be willing to spend itself all the way down.\" *I look back at you, a little more directly.* \"An example can tell me what bread is supposed to taste like. It can't forgive me for ruining the dough.\"\n\n\"What part of it are you pressing on most—the justice of it, or the necessity?\"","rolling_24h_usd":58.60921000000002,"run_id":"ab5e009b-577d-4549-9e34-bbe8ee5c2921"}
